- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on analyzing the acoustic features of speech signals generated by WaveNet.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the interpretation and visualization of a deep learning architecture for speech generation.
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing the latent representation of speech signals in WaveNet.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the unsupervised learning of acoustic features by WaveNet.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper deals with a deep learning architecture for speech generation.
